snippet.textDisplay: There was a lot of criticism on fb about Rahat Fateh Ali Khan not being as good as Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan Sahib. I want to say that Coke Studio is not about replacing the old singers. It's more of a tribute to their greatness, to our great history of art. That is why they change so much of the old songs. A fusion of the classical and the contemporary. It actually results in a revival of the old arts, not in its replacement.
